# Claude Code Portable Template

This folder contains portable assets that can be copied to any project workspace.

## What's Included

```
portable-template/
├── .claude/
│   ├── commands/       # Custom slash commands
│   ├── skills/         # Reusable skills (symlinked from global)
│   ├── templates/      # Task templates
│   └── settings.json   # Project settings template
├── CLAUDE.md           # Project instructions template
└── setup.ps1           # Windows setup script
```

## Usage

### Option 1: Copy to Project (Fresh Start)
```powershell
# From your project root:
cp -r ~/.claude/portable-template/.claude .
cp ~/.claude/portable-template/CLAUDE.md .
```

### Option 2: Symlink Skills (Shared Updates)
```powershell
# From your project root:
mkdir .claude
# Copy commands (project-specific customization)
cp -r ~/.claude/portable-template/.claude/commands .claude/
# Symlink skills (shared across projects)
New-Item -ItemType SymbolicLink -Path ".claude/skills" -Target "$env:USERPROFILE\.claude\skills"
```

### Option 3: Run Setup Script
```powershell
# From your project root:
~/.claude/portable-template/setup.ps1 -ProjectPath .
```

## Customization

After copying, customize these files for your project:
1. `CLAUDE.md` - Add project-specific instructions, stack info, conventions
2. `.claude/commands/` - Add project-specific slash commands
3. `.claude/settings.json` - Configure permissions and plugins

## What NOT to Copy

These stay in `~/.claude/` (global):
- `.claude.json` - Auth tokens, MCP servers
- `history.jsonl` - Conversation history
- `plans/` - Session-specific plans
- `projects/` - Per-project state
